text: Eleanore Cammack "Cammie" King (5 August 1934 â€“ 1 September 2010) was an American actress. Her acting career was short, but with notable movies. She played Bonnie Blue Butler in Gone with the Wind in 1939. She provided the voice for the fawn Faline in the Disney movie Bambi in 1942. King was born in Los Angeles.
